Proportion Variance Explained

# calculate variance of each component divided by the variance explained by all components (proportion of variance explained)
pve <- pca_out$sdev^2/sum(pca_out$sdev^2) 

# plot

Classification Models

# split 80-20 train-test
set.seed(1)

df_full = df_full %>%
  transform(Potability = as.factor(Potability))

n_rows <- nrow(df_full)
dt <- sort(sample(n_rows, n_rows*0.80))
train <- df_full[dt,]
test <- df_full[-dt,]

Logistic regression

# logistic regression model using regular data
logistic_model <- glm(Potability ~ ., data = train, family = binomial)
summary(logistic_model)

## Number of Fisher Scoring iterations: 4
# predicting with regular logistic model
logistic_preds <- predict(logistic_model, test, type = "response")

# predicted as "potable" if predicted liklihood of potability is greater than 0.5
pred_potable <- logistic_preds > 0.5

# converted actual potability labels into boolean (so it matches prediction format)
true_potable <- ifelse(test$Potability == 1, TRUE, FALSE)

# produces confusion matrix
print("Confusion matrix:")
## [1] "Confusion matrix:"
table(pred_potable, true_potable)
##             true_potable
## pred_potable FALSE TRUE
##        FALSE   400  255
##        TRUE      1    0
# produces error rate
print("Error rate:")
## [1] "Error rate:"
1 - mean(pred_potable == true_potable)
## [1] 0.3902439
tab <- table(pred_potable, true_potable)

rec = tab[4]/(tab[3]+tab[4])
pre = tab[4]/(tab[4]+tab[2])
speci = tab[1]/(tab[1]+tab[2])
acu = (tab[1]+tab[4])/(tab[1]+tab[2]+tab[3]+tab[4])
err_rate = (tab[2]+tab[3])/(tab[1]+tab[2]+tab[3]+tab[4])

draw_confusion_matrix <- function(cm) {

  layout(matrix(c(1,1,2)))
  par(mar=c(2,2,2,2))
  plot(c(100, 345), c(300, 450), type = "n", xlab="", ylab="", xaxt='n', yaxt='n')
  title('CONFUSION MATRIX', cex.main=2)

  # create the matrix 
  rect(150, 430, 240, 370, col='#3F97D0')
  text(195, 435, 'Not Safe', cex=1.2)
  rect(250, 430, 340, 370, col='#F7AD50')
  text(295, 435, 'Safe', cex=1.2)
  text(125, 370, 'Predicted', cex=1.3, srt=90, font=2)
  text(245, 450, 'Actual', cex=1.3, font=2)
  rect(150, 305, 240, 365, col='#F7AD50')
  rect(250, 305, 340, 365, col='#3F97D0')
  text(140, 400, 'Not Safe', cex=1.2, srt=90)
  text(140, 335, 'Safe', cex=1.2, srt=90)

  # add in the cm results 
  text(195, 400, tab[1], cex=1.6, font=2, col='white')
  text(195, 335, tab[2], cex=1.6, font=2, col='white')
  text(295, 400, tab[3], cex=1.6, font=2, col='white')
  text(295, 335, tab[4], cex=1.6, font=2, col='white')

   # add in the specifics 
   plot(c(100, 0), c(100, 0), type = "n", xlab="", ylab="", main = "DETAILS", xaxt='n', yaxt='n')
   text(10, 85, "Sensitivity", cex=1.2, font=2)
   text(10, 70, format(round(rec,3),nsmall =3), cex=1.2)
   text(30, 85, "Specificity", cex=1.2, font=2)
   text(30, 70, format(round(speci,3),nsmall =3), cex=1.2)
   text(50, 85, "Precision", cex=1.2, font=2)
   text(50, 70, format(round(pre,3),nsmall =3), cex=1.2)
   text(70, 85, "Recall", cex=1.2, font=2)
   text(70, 70, format(round(rec,3),nsmall =3), cex=1.2)
   text(90, 85, "F1", cex=1.2, font=2)
   text(90, 70, format(round( (2 * (rec * pre) ) / (rec + pre) ,3),nsmall =3), cex=1.2)
   # add in the accuracy information 
   text(30, 35,  "Accuracy", cex=1.5, font=2)
   text(30, 20, format(round(acu,3),nsmall =3), cex=1.2)
   text(70, 35, "Error Rate", cex=1.5, font=2)
   text(70, 20, format(round(err_rate,3),nsmall =3), cex=1.2)
}  

draw_confusion_matrix(cm)

draw_confusion_matrix <- function(cm) {

  layout(matrix(c(1,1,2)))
  par(mar=c(2,2,2,2))
  plot(c(100, 345), c(300, 450), type = "n", xlab="", ylab="", xaxt='n', yaxt='n')
  title('CONFUSION MATRIX', cex.main=2)

  # create the matrix
  rect(150, 430, 240, 370, col='#3F97D0')
  text(195, 435, 'No', cex=1.2)
  rect(250, 430, 340, 370, col='#F7AD50')
  text(295, 435, 'Yes', cex=1.2)
  text(125, 370, 'Predicted', cex=1.3, srt=90, font=2)
  text(245, 450, 'Actual', cex=1.3, font=2)
  rect(150, 305, 240, 365, col='#F7AD50')
  rect(250, 305, 340, 365, col='#3F97D0')
  text(140, 400, 'No', cex=1.2, srt=90)
  text(140, 335, 'Yes', cex=1.2, srt=90)

  # add in the cm results
  res <- as.numeric(cm$table)
  text(195, 400, res[1], cex=1.6, font=2, col='white')
  text(195, 335, res[2], cex=1.6, font=2, col='white')
  text(295, 400, res[3], cex=1.6, font=2, col='white')
  text(295, 335, res[4], cex=1.6, font=2, col='white')

  # add in the specifics
  plot(c(100, 0), c(100, 0), type = "n", xlab="", ylab="", main = "DETAILS", xaxt='n', yaxt='n')
  text(10, 85, names(cm$byClass[1]), cex=1.2, font=2)
  text(10, 70, round(as.numeric(cm$byClass[1]), 3), cex=1.2)
  text(30, 85, names(cm$byClass[2]), cex=1.2, font=2)
  text(30, 70, round(as.numeric(cm$byClass[2]), 3), cex=1.2)
  text(50, 85, names(cm$byClass[5]), cex=1.2, font=2)
  text(50, 70, round(as.numeric(cm$byClass[5]), 3), cex=1.2)
  text(70, 85, names(cm$byClass[6]), cex=1.2, font=2)
  text(70, 70, round(as.numeric(cm$byClass[6]), 3), cex=1.2)
  text(90, 85, names(cm$byClass[7]), cex=1.2, font=2)
  text(90, 70, round(as.numeric(cm$byClass[7]), 3), cex=1.2)

  # add in the accuracy information
  text(30, 35, names(cm$overall[1]), cex=1.5, font=2)
  text(30, 20, round(as.numeric(cm$overall[1]), 3), cex=1.4)
  text(70, 35, names(cm$overall[2]), cex=1.5, font=2)
  text(70, 20, round(as.numeric(cm$overall[2]), 3), cex=1.4)
}  

draw_confusion_matrix(cm)

Importance Plot

## Ref: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/61486153/customizing-importance-plot-r

#create importance plot
imp = as.data.frame(importance(rf))
imp = cbind(vars=rownames(imp), imp)
imp = imp[order(imp$MeanDecreaseAccuracy),]
imp$vars = factor(imp$vars, levels=unique(imp$vars))

imp %>%
  pivot_longer(cols=matches("Mean")) %>%
  ggplot(aes(value, vars)) +
  ggtitle("Variable Importance") +
  geom_col() +
  geom_text(aes(label=round(value), x=0.5*value), size=3, colour="white") +
  facet_grid(. ~ name, scales="free_x") +
  scale_x_continuous(expand=expansion(c(0,0.04))) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(panel.grid.minor=element_blank(),
        panel.grid.major=element_blank(),
        axis.title=element_blank(),
        plot.title=element_text( hjust=0.5, vjust=0.5, face='bold'))

KNN Classifier

# set up k-nearest neighbors algorithm
train_scale <- scale(train[, 1:9])
test_scale <- scale(test[, 1:9])
# Tune k for accuracy, precision, and/or recall
set.seed(1)
Accuracy = numeric(50)
Precision = numeric(50)
Recall = numeric(50)
F1 = numeric(50)
k = 1:50

for (i in k)
{
  pred.knn <- knn(train = train_scale, test = test_scale, cl = train$Potability, k=i)
  Accuracy[i]= mean(pred.knn == test$Potability)
  Precision[i] <- posPredValue(pred.knn, test$Potability, positive="1")
  Recall[i] <- sensitivity(pred.knn, test$Potability, positive="1")
  F1[i] = (2 * Precision[i] * Recall[i]) / (Precision[i] + Recall[i])
}

plot(k, Accuracy
     ,main = "Accuracy vs K values"
     ,xlab = "K values"
     ,ylab = "Accuracy")

plot(k, Precision
      ,main = "Precision vs K values"
     ,xlab = "K values"
     ,ylab = "Precision")

plot(k, Recall
      ,main = "Recall vs K values"
     ,xlab = "K values"
     ,ylab = "Recall")

plot(k, F1
      ,main = "F1 Score vs K values"
     ,xlab = "K values"
     ,ylab = "F1 Score")

# model with best testing accuracy
set.seed(1)
test.knn = knn(train = train_scale, test = test_scale, cl = train$Potability, k=21)

a = confusionMatrix(test.knn, test$Potability, mode = "everything", positive="1")
draw_confusion_matrix(a)
